Hi,

Labels (TTF) have an issue using v3.7 beta (v3 being at commit 85af18f6341d55a1e22f46cf0754fb167af22f49).
If you enable either shadow or outline, characters are not correctly displayed as see on this screenshot comparing v3.6 (top) and v3.7 (bottom) :
![buglabel](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4882169/8406114/a02ce18e-1e59-11e5-8190-e48bd8ce23e1.PNG)

Some pixels are tunctated at the top, and chars are too tighly packed (see how 'r' is overlapping inside the outline of 'l').

You can simply reproduce by modifying the template project, replacing the label by this:
    auto label = Label::createWithTTF("Hello World", "fonts/Marker Felt.ttf", 70);
    label->setTextColor(Color4B(50, 50, 0, 255));
    label->enableShadow(Color4B::RED, Size(3, -3), 3);
    label->enableOutline(Color4B::WHITE, 3);
